.TH "nfp_cpp_area_alloc" 9 "nfp_cpp_area_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nfp_cpp_area_alloc \- allocate a new CPP area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct nfp_cpp_area *" nfp_cpp_area_alloc
.BI "(struct nfp_cpp *cpp "  ","
.BI "u32 dest "  ","
.BI "unsigned long long address "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpp" 12
CPP handle
.IP "dest" 12
CPP id
.IP "address" 12
Start address on CPP target
.IP "size" 12
Size of area in bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate and initialize a CPP area structure.  The area must later
be locked down with an 'acquire' before it can be safely accessed.
.SH "NOTE"
\fIaddress\fP and \fIsize\fP must be 32-bit aligned values.
.SH "RETURN"
NFP CPP Area handle, or NULL
